oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Real photo postcard from Milton Calliham to Mrs. L. C. Lee
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Postcard from Milton Calliham to his sister, Mrs. Louise C. Lee in Fulton, Ky., January 11th, 1919. "Dear sister Louise, A nice little photo of myself. Will send more when I get them. Write me more often, and tell me the news. I am o.k. in the best of health. With love to you." On the front of the postcard is written "Three Ace's" and all three men appear to be American pilots.
